  "eprint": {
    "title": "On the security of the BCTV Pinocchio zk-SNARK variant",
    "authors": [
      {
        "name": "Ariel Gabizon",
        "email": "gabizon@gmail",
        "affiliation": ""
      }
    ],
    "abstract": "The main result of this note is a severe flaw in the description of the zk-SNARK in [BCTV14].\nThe flaw stems from including redundant elements in the CRS, as compared to that of the original Pinocchio protocol [PHGR16], which are vital not to expose.\nThe flaw enables creating a proof of knowledge for *any* public input given a valid proof for *some* public input.\nWe also provide a proof of security for the [BCTV14] zk-SNARK in the generic group model, when these elements are excluded from the CRS, provided a certain linear algebraic condition is satisfied by the QAP polynomials.",
    "keywords": [
      "zk-SNARKs"
    ],
    "category": "Cryptographic protocols",
    "publication_info": "Preprint. MINOR revision.",
    "last_updated": "2019-02-13",
